The Great British Bake Off: An Extra Slice - Series 2: Episode 7

It is week seven in the Great British Bake Off tent and just six bakers remain. Joining host Jo Brand in the An Extra Slice studio are three celebrity Bake Off fans - Michel Roux Jnr, David Baddiel and historian Ruth Goodman - eager to chew over the latest goings-on in the tent.

Jo and her guests debate which bakers were victorious in Victorian week, as well as tasting bakes brought in by the studio audience and looking at pictures of viewer bakes from home - from the incredible to the frankly inedible.

There is an interview with the latest baker to leave the tent, as well as unseen footage from the BBC One show. Jo gets the panel's take on the remaining bakers and their Victorian bakes. Who rose to the occasion in the raised game pie signature bake? Which baker served up a faultless tennis cake in the technical?

And what will the panel make of this week's charlotte russe showstopper?

The Great British Bake Off: An Extra Slice - perfect if you can't resist a second helping
